cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.IR. 

The paper deals with video understanding, specifically dense video captioning, which involves both visual and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a two-level hierarchical captioning module, which falls under the category of natural language processing, making cs.CL (Computation and Language) another likely category. The use of convolutional layers and pooling techniques for feature extraction suggests the category of cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also presents improved results on a large-scale dataset, indicating the use of machine learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another possible category. Finally, the paper deals with event detection and description, which falls under the category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
